    <div class="container">
        <h2>What is this?</h2>
        <p class="lead">
            Node.js hackathon starter template with:
            <ul>
                <li><b>Express</b> for a server and any API routes.</li>
                <li><b>TypeScript</b> for better JS.</li>
                <li><b>Nodemon</b> for hot-reloading.</li>
                <li><b>Handlebars</b> for server-side HTML templating.</li>
                <li><b>Bootstrap</b> so you don't waste time styling your website.</li>
                <li><b>jQuery Slim</b> because Bootstrap includes it.</li>
            </ul>
        </p>
        <hr>
        <h2>Set Up?</h2>
        <p class="lead">
            Getting started with the template is really easy!
            <ol>
                <li>Click <a href="https://github.com/raghav-misra/hackathon-starter/generate">here</a> and create a new repo with this template.</li>
                <li>Clone the repo to your local machine.</li>
                <li>Install all the dependencies by running <code>npm i</code>.</li>
                <li>Now you're all set up!</li>
            </ol>
        </p>
        <p class="lead">
            <b>OR</b><br>
            <a href=""><img alt="Run on Replit" src="assets/replit.svg"></a>
            <p>Use <a href="https://repl.it">repl.it</a> to get up and running immediately!</p>
        </p>
            
            
        <hr>
        <h2>User Guide:</h2>
        <p class="lead">
            NPM scripts included by default.
            <ol>
                <li>Use <code>npm start</code> to start the Express server.</li>
                <li>Use <code>npm test</code> to start the server with Nodemon hot-reloading.</li>
                <li>Use <code>npm run build</code> to compile the frontend TypeScript into JS.</li>
            </ol>
        </p>
        <hr>
        <h2>Happy Hacking!</h2>
